{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"650940b8-5086-4d16-b032-af92f6c70ab6","content":"In xUnit.net v3 with MTP, the VSTest-style `--filter` syntax changes. Here's the translation:\n\n**Old (v2 / VSTest):**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n**New (v3 / MTP):**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n…actually still works **but only if you add the VSTest bridge**. Without it, MTP uses its own filter syntax:\n\n```\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\nOr, to keep using the familiar VSTest filter expression, add the compatibility adapter to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.VSTestBridge\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n```\n\n**Summary of MTP-native `--treenode-filter` syntax:**\n\n| VSTest filter | MTP tree-node filter |\n|---|---|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` | `/**/*IntegrationTests*` |\n| `Category=Smoke` | `[Category=Smoke]` |\n| Combined with `&` | `/**/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]` |\n\nPick whichever approach fits your migration timeline—the bridge for a drop-in replacement, or the native syntax to go all-in on MTP.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2f5e6c20-5534-492b-96bc-08db5ccc4970","outputTokens":361,"requestId":"BD26:2EAB99:1C7046B:202C147:6A07C5F7"},"id":"ed42f2d2-3478-43d8-abae-a247282b83fe","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:18:56.346Z","parentId":"fed0aa85-765c-4069-b228-61b0d9dd75a1"}
